'''''The Grohl Sessions, Vol. 1''''' is an [[extended play]] which was released by the [[Zac Brown Band]] on December 10, 2013. Originally released only to digital retailers, it was physically released on May 19, 2014. The physical release includes a 45-minute DVD on the creation of the album.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://theboot.com/zac-brown-band-grohl-sessions-vol-1-cd-dvd/ |title=Zac Brown Band Announce 'The Grohl Sessions Vol. 1' CD + DVD |publisher=Theboot.com |date=2014-05-07 |accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref> Included on the album is the single "[[All Alright]]", which was sent to radio on April 28, 2014.

==Content==
''The Grohl Sessions, Vol. 1'' is a four track extended play by the [[Zac Brown Band]]. Its four tracks are "Day for the Dead", "The Muse", "Let It Rain", and "[[All Alright]]".

In an interview with ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', producer [[Dave Grohl]] stated, "They're unbelievable, the band is so good they can be tracked live; we didn't fuck with computers, we tracked live, four-part harmonies around one microphone. It's rocking. People are like, 'Oh, it's country.' 'No, it's not, it's like [[The Allman Brothers Band|the Allman Brothers]].' 'No, it's not, it's jam band.' I don't even know what you would call it, it's fucking great."<ref>{{cite web|author=Kory Grow |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/zac-brown-band-and-dave-grohl-to-release-songs-in-december-20131126 |title=Zac Brown Band and Dave Grohl to Release Songs in December &#124; Music News |publisher=Rolling Stone |date=2013-11-26 |accessdate=2014-05-14}}</ref>

